Three Gorges Falls Most in Almost 2 Month After Reporting Loss

-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 
2011-04-18T08:08:45Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-18/three-gorges-falls-most-in-almost-2-month-after-reporting-loss.html
Chongqing Three Gorges Water
Conservancy and Electric Power Co. fell the most in almost two
months after the company posted a loss of 5.49 million yuan
($840,890) for the first quarter.  The hydroelectric power company fell 5.9 percent to 17.34
yuan in  Shanghai , the biggest one-day decline since Feb. 22.
 China ’s benchmark Shanghai Composite Index gained 0.2 percent.  The 5.49 million yuan net loss Chongqing Three Gorges
reported for the first quarter was more than nine times the loss
it reported a year earlier, the company said in a statement to
Shanghai’s stock exchange after the market’s close on April 15.
Chongqing Three Gorges’s shares have increased 39 percent this
year, compared with a 9 percent gain for the Shanghai Composite
Index.  --Penny Peng. Editor:  John Liu   To contact Bloomberg News staff for this story:
